<L>__{interior the hall}
<A>__{gingerly balancing the cup and saucer, jim approaches the door to the children's room. with split second timing, he pauses as the door flies open and joan, in her bathrobe, towel in hand, rushes out and past him down the hall. she disappears into the bathroom. jim carefully proceeds down the hall and, as he reaches the bathroom, deftly steps to the left as the door bursts open and betsy flies by on the way back to her bedroom. all this is done with a timing and shifting of hips of which knute rockne might have been proud. jim continues down the hall, enters the bedroom.}
